  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I actually, when I found out his life story, I felt sorry for him more because he didn't absolutely not know anything what happened to his family, how they perished.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Till today he doesn't know if they went to a concentration camp or not.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So when-- you know, when we started really getting serious and talking, I think I felt sorry for him more than for myself, and I started to be happier and contented.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In those days, we did, even between us, and then every month more and more girls would come out, you know, to this country and to Detroit.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I-- we always met, like I said, in a Central High, in the school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And if you liked a certain person, you already made a clique.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You had your own friends.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that's how we form our group of friends and everything.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And when I got married, I felt like a million dollar.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I had my little apartment.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I had my new furniture, which I want you to see, this is it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It's 48 years-old.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And, and I was-- oh, by that time, I was working downtown, and my girlfriend introduced me and she took me to a clothing manufacturers where they made suits and coats, and I did not know how to sew.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The boss wanted to fire me because I didn't know how to hold a thimble.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And this girl, really, literally taught me how to sew, really, truly.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And that's how after that, I wind up going to night school and learned how to make drapes, which I never dreamed those days that I'm going to be in a drapery business.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And because you had no money, but I wanted something on a window, so I learned, and I went to [?",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
